	<description>
		Navigate your way through a computer simulation where you have the power to manipulate platforms by finding the right perspective. Work solo or with a friend to find your way to the next level.
	</description>

	<histories>
		<history>
			<text>V began as a final project as part of 15-466: Computer Game Programming, a course at Carnegie Mellon University. The project started with the simple theme of an escape room game that involves perspective tricks inspired by the core mechanic behind &lt;a href=&apos;http&#58;&#47;&#47;the-witness.net&#47;&apos;&gt;The Witness&lt;&#47;a&gt;, and the team began work on a co-operative game that would require puzzle-solving and exploration. V aims to encourage players to communicate, be curious, and interact with the environment in an open-ended way, and have fun doing so.</text>
		</history>
	</histories>

    <features>
		<feature>Engage in co-operative online play with your friends.</feature>
		<feature>Cross-platform support - Windows, Mac and Linux are all supported.</feature>
        <feature>Rack your brain solving challenging levels of increasing difficulty.</feature>
		<feature>Gorgeous 3D graphics with a bright, minimalist design.</feature>
    </features>

